  "prompt": "How does flitto app make money?",
  "response": "Flitto is a crowdsourced translation platform that connects users who need translations with a global community of translators. Here\u2019s how Flitto generates revenue:\n\n1. **Subscription Plans**: Flitto offers premium subscription plans for users who require frequent or high-volume translations. These plans provide benefits like faster turnaround times, access to professional translators, and discounted rates.\n\n2. **Pay-per-Use Translations**: Users can pay for individual translation requests on a per-word or per-project basis. This is ideal for users who don\u2019t need translations frequently but require high-quality results.\n\n3. **Translation API for Businesses**: Flitto offers an API that businesses can integrate into their systems to access Flitto\u2019s translation services. This is particularly useful for companies needing real-time translations for customer support, e-commerce, or other business needs.\n\n4. **Freemium Model**: While Flitto offers free translations for short texts or simple requests, users often upgrade to paid services for more complex or urgent translations.\n\n5. **Crowdsourcing Model**: Flitto\u2019s translators earn points or credits for their contributions, which can be converted into cash or used for their own translation needs. Flitto takes a commission or fee from these transactions.\n\n6. **Data Monetization**: Flitto may also monetize its vast repository of multilingual data by selling anonymized data to companies or researchers working on language-related technologies like machine translation or AI.\n\n7. **Partnerships and Enterprise Solutions**: Flitto collaborates with businesses and organizations to provide tailored translation solutions, such as localization services for apps, websites, or marketing materials.\n\nBy leveraging its global community of translators and offering flexible pricing models, Flitto serves both individual users and businesses, ensuring a steady revenue stream.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
